# CNN Accelerator Simulator
This project simulates a C++ CNN accelerator.

## Build And Run
Please unzip the .zip file first.

1. Model Training
```bash
python3 training/train_mnist_cnn.py
```
After training, the bias and weights are written to `conv1_bias.txt` and `conv1_weights.txt`.

2. Accelerator Simulation
```bash
g++ -std=c++17 -Iinclude src/*.cpp -o bitserial_sim.exe
./bitserial_sim.exe
```
After the run finishes, the results are written to `experiment_report.txt`.

## Main Run Switches
1. The main experiment settings are in [src/main.cpp].

2. The most important switches are:
```cpp
[614] const bool use_dataset_mode = true;  // true: using real mnist sample; false: using randomize data
[615] const int dataset_sample_index = 0; // load the nth image to do testing
[616] const std::string dataset_input_path = "mnist_test.csv";
[617] const std::string dataset_weight_path = "training/conv1_weight.txt";
[618] const std::string dataset_bias_path = "training/conv1_bias.txt";
```
